<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1885-03-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1885-03-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="176" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d176">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">No. 176.</seg></opener>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Becerra</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-03-10"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 10,
                                1885</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            note of the 2d instant respecting the movement of certain parties in the
                            United States, who, it is alleged, are engaged in fitting out warlike
                            expeditions against the Government of Colombia, and to inform you that
                            the attention of the proper authorities was promptly invited to the
                            subject.</p>
                        <p>Accept, &amp;c.,</p>
                        <closer><signed>T. E. BAYARD.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>